      "audio": "audio/people/015.mp3",
      "audioLocal": "audio/people/015.mp3",
      "audioSource": "tts",
      "examples": [],
      "etymology": "According to Fähnrich, from an earlier form *ქურთ- (*kurt-), from Proto-Kartvelian *kurt-, *kut-. Cognate with Mingrelian ქვირთუ (kvirtu, “thief”) and Svan ქუ̂ით (kûit), ლიქუ̂თერ (likûter, “to steal”). However Topuria considered Svan ქუ̂ით (kûit) a borrowing from Mingrelian, in which case only Proto-Georgian-Zan is reconstructible."
    },
